                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>The tablet is nscribed on <rs type="sides" key="opisthographic">both sides</rs>. The same tablet also preserves one further inscription on the same side (<ref target="i-dodone-online-37b">37B</ref>), which is related to the one on side A (<ref target="i-dodone-online-35a">35A</ref>), the latter containing the summary and the former the question. Since <ref target="i-dodone-online-37b">37B</ref> presupposes the existence of 36B, this must have been the tablet's first use. At present, side B is covered by insulating tape used to secure the two fragments together, which hampers legibility.</p>
                                    <p n="Dialect"><rs type="dialect" ref="#doric">Doric</rs></p>
                                    <p n="Alphabet"><rs type="alphabet" ref="#archaic">Archaic</rs></p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Letter height: 0.3 cm (l. 1); 0.35-0.4 cm (l. 2). As the editors note, the second line of the inscription is laid out in stoichedon style.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
